               <p>WILLIAM COTTRELL. I am a <rs id="t18310908-331-viclabel1703" type="occupation">news-vender</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-331-victim2391 t18310908-331-viclabel1703"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18310908-331-crimeloc1704">Martin-street, City-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-331-crimeloc1704" type="placeName" value="Martin-street, City-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-331-crimeloc1704" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-331-off1701 t18310908-331-crimeloc1704"></join>, in the back parlour. On the 25th of August I saw the prisoner, (who was a stranger.) in the passage, with these things loose under his arm - he dropped the handkerchief; I followed, and asked him what he had there - he said he did not know, and let them fall; they had hung over a chair in my room - the door was not locked.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BODKIN. Q. Where were you? A. I had gone down in the kitchen for about two minutes, and as I came up I saw him - I had left the door open - there was hardly time for him to take them.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-331-person2392">
                  CHARLES 
                  WALLER
               <interp inst="t18310908-331-person2392" type="surname" value="WALLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-331-person2392" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-331-person2392" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. I was called in, and took the prisoner; the things laid at his feet - he said great distress made him do it.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner received and excellent character.</p>
